CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. 19 reads: "1. Louise R. Prothro, Pet Milk Company home economist and demonstrator for The Courier Home Shows, held the audiences spell-bound with her culinary artistry. Assisting her is Mrs. Mary Ellen Nelson.  Westinghouse electric appliances, furnished by the Oakland Furniture Company, were used exclusively in all her demonstrations."
TitMainTitle: Louise R. Prothro and Mary Ellen Nelson wearing eyeglasses, standing at a cooking demonstration table with Pet Milk products, in Syria Mosque for 1957 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
